Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Importing text file and biliography", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.862554521852718*^9, 
  3.862554534393876*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"57490ca4-1da4-4ec9-aebb-\
6c12383f7396"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To create the text file use pandoc and then convert to markdown with pandoc \
-s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Hilbert_spaces.tex\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] -o \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Hilbert.txt\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] run from directory \
where file is (open folder and write cmd on address)\nAnother option is to \
use https://pandoc.org/try/ and then select latex to html, citeproc mathjax \
and rest blank but no links\nPdfs should only be one word\nCitations to \
theorems have to be searched by looking for # and manually replaced.\nIf \
citing the same document multiple times errors may occur.\n",
 StyleBox["If link contains parenthesis will do error. Find portion of text \
far from parenthesis. Check links that don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t work with ctrl \
f [ on webpage",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\nCopy equations that don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t parse to overleaf to test\nIf \
there is a ",
 StyleBox["star",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " in equation possible mess up\nIf there is something like {\\mathbb R}, \
{\\mathcal R} will mess up\nChange all Proof. to **Proof.**\nAligned wont be \
cited but align will. Indentation can also be important notebook will do it \
automatically thanks to pandoc.\n"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.862554560964918*^9, 3.862554621707685*^9}, {
   3.8626846098485312`*^9, 3.862684612366813*^9}, {3.8628156881034627`*^9, 
